      <div class="msgContentFrame">Okay, who wins? Definitely the stamina bar! <br /> <br />Lately, I've been playing my Rank 18 Glad. in parties trying to take the main blunt force of the mobs. I've noticed that this is a very limited and very difficult path to go down in terms of the stamina bar. It seems every battle has to be precise with the usage of this bar. More times than not I'm at zero stamina and I'm using it as sparingly as I possiblely can. <br /> <br />Now, it would seem to me that a Glad would first use Provoke in a party battle. So, I do and there goes Half of my gauge. <br /> <br />Then, I would guess, like always, to use your Shield. Ok, so I do that. That takes it down another quarter of the way. Leaving around 1/4 left. <br /> <br />Now, I need to place some hits on the mob, right? We all know the only thing holding that Provoke to a Glad is a piece of Bubblelicous Bubble Gum, right? So, I hit it once, well if I'm lucky, and maybe twice if I happen have some extra stamina. <br /> <br />But here's where the fun part comes in, trying to ATLEAST cast ONE defensive buff plus another Provoke and maybe get another hit in. All the while the stamina bar is still next to none. Not to mention trying to use a weapon skill and keeping your shield up to fend off some damage.  <br /> <br />Now I know I could stand around with my shield up waiting for my stamina bar to fill back up every fight. But, this just cuts WAY to much time into getting any DECENT skillpoints. Why give us ALL these defensive abilites (Defender, Rampart, Obsess, Phalanx) if we in NO way can even use 2 or 3 if we're lucky. NOT to mention even the SHIELD abilites. I can't even use basic GLAD abilites without draining my stamina bar. Think SE! Think SE!! Use SOME brain power to improve upon this, please! <br /> <br />It doesn't seem right having to choose between a Provoke to save someone's tail or an Attack just to better my GLAD with Skillpoints. &gt;&gt;BUT EITHER WAY I'M SCREWED BECAUSE I'LL BE WAITING 6 SECONDS FOR THE STAMINA BAR.&lt;&lt; <br /> <br />Ok, now this is just for the GLAD. class and I don't know if any other classes are like this or not. Please tell me if they are or aren't. To me, I would think a Marauder could just run and gun it? Maybe a Pugilist and a Lancer also? Tell me. To me this is just unfair to Glads. Expecting them to be the work horses when it comes to taking in the damage but not allowing them the means to do so. <br /> <br />Also, has anyone else experienced this with this job while partying Glad.? <br /> <br />Chow</div>
